________________________________

In samza-core/src/main/java/org/apache/samza/table/utils/TableMetricsUtil.java<https://eur04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fapache%2Fsamza%2Fpull%2F672%23discussion_r223097945&data=02%7C01%7C%7Cb43c4759baf24bdbaa5808d62aeefd32%7C84df9e7fe9f640afb435aaaaaaaaaaaa%7C1%7C0%7C636743603262673159&sdata=83mwglQhL9O52kgZtb6FXnC7rBBqdoXILR9pL6dvYUw%3D&reserved=0>:

>      Preconditions.checkNotNull(table);
     Preconditions.checkNotNull(tableId);

-    this.metricsRegistry = taskContext == null // The table is at container level, when the task
-        ? containerContext.metricsRegistry     // context passed in is null
-        : taskContext.getMetricsRegistry();
+    this.metricsRegistry = context.getTaskContext().getTaskMetricsRegistry();


Thanks. We will simplify the constructor now to just use task-level metrics, since that is the only current use case. When the container-level table functionality comes in, then this can be modified or a new path can be added.

